The '''New International Commentary on the Old Testament''' is a series of commentaries in English on the text of the [[Old Testament]] in Hebrew. It is published by the [[Wm. B. Eerdmans Publishing Company|William B. Eerdmans Publishing Company]]. The series editor is [[Robert L. Hubbard, Jr.]]<ref>{{cite web|title=New International Commentary on the Old Testament|url=http://bestcommentaries.com/series/new-international-commentary-on-the-old-testament-nicot/|publisher=bestcommentaries.com}}</ref>

''[[Christianity Today]]'' magazine included it in a list of the more significant publications and achievements of [[Evangelicalism]] in the latter half of the 20th century.<ref>{{cite news|last=Nicole|first=Roger|title=What Evangelicalism Has Accomplished|url=http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/1996/september16/6ta030.html?start=2|accessdate=January 26, 2012|newspaper=Christianity Today|date=September 16, 1996|authorlink=Roger Nicole|page=2|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090218140843/http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/1996/september16/6ta030.html?start=2 |archivedate=2009-02-18}}</ref>

